  "sw_detailed": {
    "module_name": "EgtmAtomPwm",
    "public_functions": [
      {
        "signature": "void initEgtmAtom3phInv(void)",
        "behavior_description": "Initialize a unified EGTM PWM instance to drive three complementary, center-aligned phase pairs at the requested switching frequency with configured dead-time, and a separate edge-aligned trigger output channel for ADC sampling. Implementation steps: 1) Declare all configuration structures as locals: main IfxEgtm_Pwm_Config, an array IfxEgtm_Pwm_ChannelConfig channelConfig[3] for the three logical channels (one base + two synchronous), an optional IfxEgtm_Pwm_DtmConfig dtmConfig[3] for dead-times, an IfxEgtm_Pwm_OutputConfig output[3] for signal routing/polarities, and a single IfxEgtm_Pwm_InterruptConfig interruptConfig for the base channel. Also declare a persistent module-state structure (in this module's C file) that contains: the PWM driver handle, a persistent channels array (used by the driver after init), and state arrays for dutyCycles[3], deadTimes[3], and phases[3]. 2) Call IfxEgtm_Pwm_initConfig to load defaults into the main config. 3) Populate per-channel fields directly: set logical timerCh for the three channels to SubModule_Ch_0, SubModule_Ch_1, and SubModule_Ch_2; set alignment to center for the three-phase PWM; set initial duty values to 25%, 50%, and 75% respectively; attach complementary outputs and polarity in output[]; assign rising and falling dead-time of 1 microsecond in dtmConfig[] for each complementary pair; assign the base channel’s interrupt pointer to &interruptConfig while setting the remaining channels’ interrupt pointers to NULL. For interruptConfig, set mode to pulse notification, isrProvider to cpu0, priority to 25, vmId to 0, assign periodEvent to IfxEgtm_periodEventFunction, and dutyEvent to NULL. 4) Complete the main config: target the proper cluster and ATOM submodule, set numChannels=3 (one per complementary phase pair), attach channelConfig[], set syncStart=TRUE for a synchronized start after init, set frequency to 20 kHz, and select CMU Clock 0 for the ATOM and the DTM dead-time clock sourc